article.headline: Lehigh 56, Monmouth, N.J. 39
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Marquis Hall and Rob Keefer had 12 and 11 points, respectively, to lead Lehigh to a 56-39 victory over Monmouth, N.J., on Friday. Lehigh senior captain Bryan White pulled down 13 rebounds, his third straight game of double-digit boards, bringing his career rebound total to 500. Lehigh (6-5) shot 44 percent from the floor and held Monmouth (2-10) to 28 percent from the floor. The Mountain Hawks outrebounded Monmouth 43-26 and sank 10-of-11 free throws. Hall led Lehigh with five assists, while White and Keefer registered two steals apiece. Monmouth was led by Yaniv Simpson, who hit for 11 points, while Jhamar Youngblood scored nine points and pulled down a team-best six rebounds.
